text:
Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

I am very surprised to hear a bee talk, but nevertheless I asked the bee "What do you mean?"
The bee replied "You are the queen of the bees and the bees have chosen you to rule over them."
I thought this was strange since I'm deathly allergic to bee but I was happy to be queen so I played along.
The bee then said "Your first order is to go to the meadow and make a hive." I didn't know how to make a hive the way bees do, but I did the best I could. I got some sticks and leaves and I made a hive that looked just like a little house for the bees. "How's that?" I asked the bee when I was finished.
I heard the bee say "It's very nice, but you forgot the most important thing." 
"And what's that?" I asked. And the bee said I need to put it up high in a tree so nothing can harm it. So I climbed a tree and I carefully tied my handcrafted beehive house up in the top of a tree. "There, it's safe now," I said to the bee.
The next day, I could see hundreds of bees moving into the hive. "They won't sting me will they?" I asked my new friend. 
"No, you are the queen and they will do anything for you," the bee replied. And then I had a great idea. 
"Little bee I have a favor to ask of you," I told my friend. 
"What is that?" asked the friendly bee.
"I am so allergic to a bee sting. I am willing to be your queen and I will even stay and guard the hive if you do me this one thing. Can you make me not allergic to bee stings?"
"I don't think I have the power," said the bee. "But I can travel far and wide and tell all of the bees that you are my queen and that they can never sting you."
"That would be great!", I exclaimed.  So a great deal was worked out. I kept the bees safe from harm and I was protected from being stung by bees again for the rest of my life. The end.
